stylometry: In our group project, we wanted to look at the ideal number of nurses per 12 hour shift we would need to cover all the patients.  What we aimed for was 1 nurse per 4 patients.  We found that our demand for patients per day was around 15.  So in order to find the ideal number of nurses we wanted per 12 hour shifts, we ran a simulation to see what our optimal solution was.  After doing so we came up with 5 because with this many nurses you will most likely incur not waiting or liability costs and we will have more than enough nurses to care for all the patients.  Also choosing 5 gave us the highest avg. mean profit and the lowest standard deviation.  We could have chose to go with 4 nurses which would have been the conservative way to go but in my opinion its better to overstaff especially when the demand of the patients can vary alot.  From this project, I learned that in order for a business to succeed and make more money, there is a risk involved.  You can always choose the conservative way but if you dont take risks or be aggressive then how do you know your potential as a business.
